1. mail -f ~/mbox
2. set VISUAL=/usr/bin/vim
3. set EDITOR=/usr/bin/vim
4. *
5. .
6. d doug.jones
7. mail -s"Delete this message" -a ~/.mailrc doug.jones < /dev/null
8. ~v
9. h
10. h-
11. S doug.jones
12. x
13. 
set EDITOR=/usr/bin/vim, sets the default message editor to vim
set VISUAL=/usr/bin/vim, sets the default visual editor to vim
set record=~/wwinberg/letters/mailout &
set folder=~/wwinberg/letters, together these record my outgoing mail in a directory
alias me william.winberg@syccuxas01.pcc.edu, setting a shortcut for myself to save time